      "side": 1,
      "message": "It definitely makes sense to have a period where both password storage implementations work. My thought was that I don\u0027t want to introduce too many new options and also to keep the implementation as lean as possible. Thus, I came up with the idea to keep read-only access to the external-ID based password storage, but to write to the new account-ref based storage, which then has precedence or is used in combination with the old password. That woul dat least allow a migration-less transition for active users, i.e. users that react to an announcement that everybody should rotate their password to use the new storage. This would mean less control than you suggestion, since the time of `$DATE` / `$RELEASE` would be determined by an upgrade, rather than a configuration option. It would also not provide a clean way to roll back, if the external-ID-based password was already deleted.\nI would be open for both and rather listen to what the community prefers.",
